  "text": "Energy consumption is dramatically increasing, and the global energy demand is estimated to grow by more than 85% by 2040. Fossil fuel resources provide most of the world's energy demands but are limited, and thus additional sources of energy must be considered. Biofuels have the potential to supply a portion of our society's energy demands. Biodiesel is a diesel fuel derived from animal or plant oils and is composed of methyl esters of long-chain fatty acids produced by transesterification of lipids [CITATION_1] .",
